the vagina monologues the vagina monologues please join stanford's annual production of this award winning play which was based on playwright eve ensler's interviews with more than 200 women the play explores issues of femininity sexual exploration female empowerment and more through this play women throughout the world have learned to take control of their bodies and lives showtimes at 8pm on 2 20 and at 2pm and 8pm on 2 21 more information date and time ongoing every day from february 20 2010 through february 21 2010 8 00 pm approximate duration of 1.5 hour s location annenberg auditorium located in basement of cummings art building 435 lasuen mall stanford ca 94305 map audience faculty staff alumni friends general public students members category drama theater arts sponsor stanford v day contact 816 695 2566 jassy388 stanford edu admission tickets are $10 for students and $12 for everyone else a portion of the proceeds will help support stop raping our greatest resource power to women and girls of the democratic republic of congo http drc vday org download email event print use this permalink last modified february 18 2010
